FT  18 MAR 94 / Observer: Hackneyed cab
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fed up with paying too much for your car insurance? In that case buy
yourself a pastel-coloured motor. Barry Hulbert, who runs Hill House
Hammond, one of the UK's biggest chains of high street insurance shops, says
owners of black or red vehicles may have to pay higher premiums because,
statistically, they are more likely to make a claim.
Is the implication that if all drivers of red and black cars change to
lemon, they are suddenly going to have fewer accidents? Oh well, the
insurance industry always prefers putting carts before horses.
