<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): New chips for old
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
For many upgradeable PCs, replacing the old processor chip with the latest
one is tantamount to putting a Ferrari engine in a mini - the rest of the
machine cannot cope.
Californian company General Micro Systems has now launched a machine which
connects the components on the single board with a 64 bit bus which can
transport data at a rate of 320 Megabytes a second - far faster than
required by today's processors. The Predator, sold in Europe by FPS, of
Bracknell, can handle any type of processor.
GMS: US, 909 980 4813. FPS: UK, 0344 56921.
