FT  18 MAR 94 / Ucatt attacks 'debts' rumour
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ucatt, the construction union, yesterday said that groups of trade unionists
were in collusion with employers in a 'rumour campaign' which falsely
alleged that it was about to go into liquidation, Robert Taylor writes.
Mr George Brumwell, general secretary, said: 'Our union has been subject to
vicious lies alleging either that we have gone bust or are in imminent
danger of doing so. Nothing could be further from the truth.' He did not
give details of which union or unions the individuals involved came from.
Ucatt merger talks with the TGWU general union have reached a delicate
stage. A conflict over alleged membership poaching in construction is still
going on with the AEEU engineering union.
Mr Brumwell said the 'only real financial liability' was a Pounds 1.4m
overdraft facility with Unity Trust, the union bank, which was more than
adequately covered by assets.
