</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
North Korea could still forestall a move to international sanctions if it
kept its promise quickly to allow inspection of nuclear sites, Mr Winston
Lord, US assistant secretary of state, told Congress yesterday, Reuter
reports from Washington. Talks with North Korea had been cancelled, and US
suspension of Team Spirit military exercises with South Korea was being
