<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 94 / Creditors fight BCCI pact move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Two creditors of the collapsed Bank of Credit and Commerce International
plan to use the Luxembourg courts to delay the liquidators finalising an
agreement with the government of Abu Dhabi, majority shareholder in the
bank, Andrew Jack reports.
Faisal Islamic Bank and Dr Adil Elias, a member of the BCCI creditors'
committee, have lodged an application with the court of referees in
Luxembourg to prevent the liquidators signing an agreement until after April
1. The aim is to ensure Abu Dhabi hands over all records it holds relating
to BCCI. Under a separate agreement between Abu Dhabi and the US, these must
be provided to the liquidators if an agreement has not been finalised by the
start of next month. A hearing is scheduled for Monday.
</TEXT>
