<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 94 / International Company News: JP Morgan to support Banesto
rescue scheme
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WHITE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A potential obstacle for the rescue plan being mounted for Banco Espanol de
Credito (Banesto) was removed yesterday when J. P. Morgan of the US
confirmed it would support the scheme at a shareholders' meeting on March
26.
The restructuring plan drawn up by the Bank of Spain means that the 7.9 per
cent stake held by J. P. Morgan-managed Corsair Fund, the largest single
shareholding in the bank, will be diluted to 4.5 per cent as a result of the
writing down of the nominal share value from Pta700 to Pta400.
J. P. Morgan advised the former Banesto chairman Mr Mario Conde, who was
dismissed by the Bank of Spain in December after inspectors found the bank
had greatly over-valued its assets. Auditors have calculated the 'hole' in
Banesto's balance sheet at Pta605bn (Dollars 4.36bn).
The US bank said it had not yet decided whether to make a further investment
in Banesto following the capitalisation plan in order to restore the size of
its holding.
</TEXT>
