FT  17 MAR 94 / International Company News: Pasminco sells mine interest
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pasminco, the Australian zinc and lead producer, is selling a 40 per cent
interest in the Elura zinc/lead mine in New South Wales to Korea Zinc
Company for ADollars 40m (USDollars 28.7m).
The price will be paid in two instalments: ADollars 27m when the deal is
completed, and a further ADollars 13m when the mine is upgraded to allow it
to operate at its 'installed' capacity of 1.2m tonnes of ore a year. It
currently operates at only around 800,000 tonnes a year.
Once back to installed capacity, Pasminco will take 60 per cent of the
output to supply its Australian smelters, while Korea Zinc will use the
remainder to supply zinc and lead smelters in Korea.
