<TEXT>
Caterpillar, the US heavy equipment manufacturer, has signed a joint venture
agreement with China's leading diesel engine maker to build engines in
China, writes Martin Dickson.
Caterpillar will be the majority partner in the venture with Shanghai Diesel
Engine.
Under a previous agreement between the two companies, engines were built in
China with Caterpillar technology, but sold under a different trademark.
They will now be marketed in China as Caterpillar engines.
