<TEXT>
Brascan, a key holding company in the Edper-Hees group, has settled a
dispute with an international banking consortium, writes Robert Gibbens in
Montreal.
It will repay immediately USDollars 62.5m or 12.5 per cent of Dollars 500m
owed to 10 foreign banks led by Chemical Bank of the US.
A lawsuit begun in the UK by the banks has been dropped and Brascan will
consult the banks before making any further significant asset sales. Another
Dollars 12.5m will be paid to Germany's Commerzbank, which is owed another
Dollars 100m.
