<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 94 / UK Company News: More acquisitions for Coats
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Neville Bain, chief executive of Coats Viyella, Europe's largest textiles
company, and Sir David Alliance, chairman, have set their sights on more
acquisitions this year, writes Daniel Green.
New companies made a strong contribution to Coats' annual results published
yesterday. The company has brought gearing down to 31 per cent, the level it
was three years ago before it took over Tootal, the thread maker, in a
Pounds 252m hostile bid.
'The acquisitions are likely to be under Pounds 50m each', said Mr Bain,
adding that a figure as high as Pounds 100m was possible.
Target businesses are likely to be in the company's biggest areas of
business: thread, clothing, homewares and precision engineering outside the
UK.
The company also announced yesterday the Dollars 12.5m (Pounds 8.5m)
purchase of a US precision plastics company, Precision Engineering of
Minneapolis, Minnesota.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Coats Viyella.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P2253 Knit Outerwear Mills.
    P2211 Broadwoven Fabric Mills, Cotton.
