downturn in sales in the run up to the Chancellor's autumn Budget.
However, for the opening 14 weeks of the current year sales were ahead of
budget. A 'clear programme' for the next stage of recovery in 1994 was also
in hand.
Losses per share for the year emerged at 3.11p (14.16p for the 78 weeks).
