<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 94 / Labour MPs in pivotal position
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Many council leaders who oppose the government's review of local-authority
responsibilities have started lobbying Labour MPs, who have been placed in a
pivotal position by dissension among Tories.
In the past week the Labour leaders of 38 English and Welsh county councils
have called on the party to abandon its support for the review, claiming it
will be a 'political disaster'. But the leaders of more than 100 Labour-run
district councils have urged the party's MPs not to drop their strong
support for unitary councils, which combine the present functions of
districts and councils.
</TEXT>
